benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{accountEmailId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account email audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: TC01 covers successful retrieval with valid IDs; TC10 covers extra query parameters; TC11 covers large audit log sets; TC15 covers ordering expectation; TC16 ensures schema compatibility; TC17 considers accessibility implications; TC02 covers empty audit log scenario; TC03/TC04/TC05/TC06/TC07/TC08/TC09 cover various error/edge cases; TC12 covers downstream timeout behavior; TC13/TC14 cover basic security input validation; TC18/TC19 cover state variation scenarios
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for API-supported pagination (e.g., page/size, cursors) or explicit pagination controls beyond large data mention.
Authorization: Tests focus on authentication (401) but do not include authorization failures (e.g., 403) for insufficient privileges.
Rate Limiting: No tests validating throttling or rate limiting behavior.
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting ETag/Cache-Control/Last-Modified headers or cache semantics.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify correct handling of page size, page number, and total counts for large datasets.
Add authorization failure scenario (403) to ensure proper handling when user is authenticated but lacks permission.
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests to confirm graceful handling under high request load.
Add tests to validate caching headers and behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation on data changes.
